HEADWORD: Finsen light
<hw>Fin"sen light</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After Prof. Niels R.
<etsep>Finsen</etsep> (b. 1860), Danish physician.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Highly actinic light, derived from sunlight or
from some form of electric lamp, used in the treatment of lupus and
other cutaneous affections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fint</ent>⟦br⟧
